## Link to this sectionLogging#

In training a YOLO26 model, you might find it valuable to keep track of the model's performance over time. This is where logging comes into play. Ultralytics YOLO provides support for three types of loggers - [Comet](/integrations/comet), [ClearML](/integrations/clearml), and [TensorBoard](/integrations/tensorboard).

To use a logger, select it from the dropdown menu in the code snippet above and run it. The chosen logger will be installed and initialized.

### Link to this sectionComet#

[Comet](/integrations/comet) is a platform that allows data scientists and developers to track, compare, explain and optimize experiments and models. It provides functionalities such as real-time metrics, code diffs, and hyperparameters tracking.

To use Comet:

Example
    
    
    # pip install comet_ml
    import comet_ml
    
    comet_ml.init()

